Diana and Jason met the fall of their senior year at Dartmouth

Diana was on "door duty" for a sorority party. The following week, they had their first date at food court ("foco"). They talked for 3 hours and bonded over having the most amazing grandparents and commiserating over how few Yiddish words they knew

After graduation, Jason went to New York and started his career at Etsy as a software engineer. Diana started on the medical track before deciding there were far too many doctors in her family already. She then discovered her passion for product management as a way to tackle some of the biggest systemic problems in our society.  

They settled into the East Village with a roommate (Hi Jimmy) and six months later, road-tripped up to Rochester and came back with a wonderful puppy, Walle, this bundle of fluff with a goofy personality. He has since taught them so much about themselves and what it means to be a family.

That June, the three of them drove up to Dartmouth for Jason's 5 year reunion and the Quechee Hot Air Balloon Festival. Diana had grown up admiring the hot air balloon photos her Grandma Alese and Grandpa Mort had taken! It was while looking down at the Vermont farmland that Jason proposed.

They are so excited to share this moment with close friends and family who have supported them throughout their journey.

Safe travels!
